{"title":"Revel introduces their first rigid bike: the Revel Rover gravel bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/revel-introduces-their-first-rigid-bike-the-revel-rover-gravel-bike/","date":1638457327000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140152/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-8.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-279716\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Revel Bikes is best known for their mountain bikes. Partially because that’s all they’ve offered, and partially because they’re so darn good. Now, the company has taken a step in a new direction by introducing their first fully rigid bike—a carbon gravel bike naturally.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike in mint\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140205/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-13-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Revel isn’t the first mountain bike company to introduce a gravel bike, and they surely won’t be the last. You can chalk that up to ‘gravel’ being a pretty vague term these days, and there being a subset of gravel bikes that are built for use on singletrack as much as they are open fire road. Truthfully, this isn’t much of a stretch for Revel anyway. They’ve already been building rad gravel bikes, just out of titanium for their sister brand Why Cycles. Revel’s team tells us they wanted a carbon version of the R+ though, so they went to work on a carbon option from Revel.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike front fork tire clearance\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140154/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-9-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>To build a gravel bike worthy of the Revel marque, they started with a full carbon frame and fork and built it with clearance for big 700c x 50mm tires—though complete bikes will ship with Maxxis Rambler 700c x 40mm.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike frame tire clearance\" width=\"1200\" height=\"853\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10-297x211.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10-800x569.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10-120x85.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140156/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-10-768x546.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike SRAM UDH\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140111/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>To allow for that massive tire or mud clearance while maintaining the clearance for a 46t chainring, the Rover is built with a drop chainstay design with a threaded bottom bracket shell. Out back there is a 142mm rear axle with a SRAM UDH. Additional frame details include a 27.2mm seat post diameter, IS42/52 headset, and 140/160mm flat mount brakes.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike geometry\" width=\"2560\" height=\"891\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-297x103.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-800x278.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-120x42.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-768x267.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-1536x535.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/02095447/Geo-Charts-rover-updated-12-2048x713.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></a></p><p>Offered in five sizes, the Rover is the first Revel to be offered with an XXL option.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike Mint\" width=\"1200\" height=\"767\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7-297x190.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7-800x511.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7-120x77.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140122/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-7-768x491.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5.jpg\" alt=\"Revel Rover carbon gravel bike T-1000\" width=\"1200\" height=\"733\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5-297x181.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5-800x489.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5-120x73.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140117/Revel-Rover-carbon-gravel-bike-2022-5-768x469.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140145/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-5-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"888\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4-297x220.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4-800x592.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4-120x89.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01140143/Revel-Rover-gravel-bike-carbon-4-768x568.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>It’s also offered in the two most popular Revel colors—Mint and T-1000. Rovers won’t start shipping until February 15, 2022, but when they do, there will be framest and complete build options. Framesets will go for $2,400, and there will be a SRAM Rival build for $3,999, a Shimano GRX build for $4,600, and a SRAM RED eTap AXS build for $8,199.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.revelbikes.com/our-bikes/rover-gravel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>revelbikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3f8ab0d9b9fdbc29c1c1af5d223ccbf2dc900786ab60d5732630fff3a2edbb4e","category":"Cycling"}